\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line Boston Media House \'28Pty\'29 Ltd is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education institution\'2C and is accredited to offer a Diploma in Media Practice by the HEQC. The Bachelor of Business Administrationin Media Operations Management programme was tabled during the Accreditation Committee Meeting of 27 July 2011 and was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A\line \line 1. The programme design is intrinsically flawed and does not meet the requirements of the HEQF in terms of being a well-designed\'2C coherent programme. The modules are difficult to evaluate but they do not meet the cognitive demands as required by an NQF level 8 qualification. \'28 Criteria 1 \'26 3\'29\line \line 2. The institution has not clarified the experiential learning component sufficiently. This process is not formally finalised\'2C there are no formal contracts\'2Fagreements in place and there is no mention made of how exactly industry provides feedback regarding course content.  \'28 Criteria 1\'29\line \line 3. Some of the material prescribed for certain modules needs to be reviewed\'2C as it is either outdated or more appropriate material is available. \'28 Criteria 1\'29\line \line 4. The institution has not provided sufficient detail on the learning progression from one academic year to the next. Although it is stated that students will have the opportunity to repeat a module whilst continuing with other modules\'2C it is not clear how many modules may be repeated in one academic year.\line \'28 Criteria 6\'29\line \line 5. The institution has not provided sufficient details on tutorials as a learning activity and who will be used as tutorial staff. \'28 Criteria 3\'29\line \line 6. The institution has not provided sufficient clarification on how it will ensure that as student numbers increase and as students\'E2\'80\'99 progress through the programme\'2C more staff will be appointed. \'28 Criteria  3\'29\line \line 7. The institution has not provided sufficient information on how expansion of infrastructure will be made a priority as student number grow. \'28 Criteria 7\'29\line \line The institution submitted a representation. \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
