\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator noted that it would appear that the institution had withheld crucial information in its original submission \'E2\'80\'93 inclusion of which would have pre-empted the concerns that the original Evaluator Panel was obliged to raise. It is stated that the representations are comprehensive and adequately clarify areas of concern raised legitimately by the original Evaluator Panel.\line The evaluator of the representation has compared the representation with the original programme submission and observed that clarification has been provided. Modules have been re-designated in terms of fundamental and core. The evaluator stated that the representation and clarifications made indicate that the programme meets the cognitive demands as required by an NQF level 8 qualification. The evaluator is satisfied that the representation clarifies what the institution may have intended in the original submission but had not provided sufficient detail and academic logic to the satisfaction of the original Evaluator Panel.  \line As far as WIL is concerned the evaluator refers to the presentation of a comprehensive document and annexures on Experiential Learning and states that it addresses a shortcoming that had been picked up by the original Evaluator Panel. The institution\'E2\'80\'99s practices with regard to Experiential Learning appear to be sound and implementable.\line In terms of learning material the evaluator felt that the institution has demonstrated that material for the programme is updated\'2C appropriate and adequate. The availability of electronic resources adds significant value to the programme resource-base.\line \line The reason forwarded that the institution has not provided sufficient detail on the learning progression from one academic year to the next was also viewed as being met by the evaluator and it is stated that the institution has furnished clarification that demonstrates an appreciation of the source of concerns raised by the previous panel and provided details on progression from one year level to the next. Other concerns were also satisfied by the provisioning of further details by the institution.\line \line It would appear that the reasons forwarded for not accrediting the programme have been addressed with the additional information that was provided. The Directorate supports the recommendation that the programme should be accredited. \line \line \cell \pard 

